definitions.definition: A small community , often rural , whose members share in the ownership of property, and in the division of labour ; the members of such a community.
A local political division in many European countries as well as their former colonies (such as Chile and Vietnam ).
A self-governing city or league of citizens .

main_definition: A small community , often rural , whose members share in the ownership of property, and in the division of labour ; the members of such a community.
secondary_definitions: A local political division in many European countries as well as their former colonies (such as Chile and Vietnam ).
( obsolete ) The commonalty ; the common people.
( uncountable , obsolete ) Communion ; sympathetic conversation between friends.
( historical ) A self-governing city or league of citizens .
